# Day 19 - Partition Equal Subset Sum (Dynamic Programming)

## Problem

**LeetCode 416 - Partition Equal Subset Sum**

Given an integer array `nums`, determine if it can be partitioned into two subsets such that the sum of elements in both subsets is equal.

---

## Approaches Covered

1. Recursion
2. Memoization
3. Tabulation
4. Space Optimization

---

## Algorithm

1. Compute the total sum of the array.
2. If the total sum is odd, return `false`.
3. Otherwise, the problem reduces to checking whether a subset with sum `totalSum / 2` exists.
4. Solve it using the classic Subset Sum DP.

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | O(2ⁿ) | O(n) |
| Memoization | O(n × target) | O(n × target) |
| Tabulation | O(n × target) | O(n × target) |
| Space Optimized | O(n × target) | O(target) |

